DEFINITIONS:

The "Aeris Packages" is an open project sponsored by Aeris Network.

End User - The "End User" is defined as any person that willingly and 
lawfully subscribes to an Aeris Packages Repository in order to install 
Software via an Aeris installation package.  Also referred to as 'User'.

Upstream Vendor - An "Upstream Vendor" is any software company or 
Individual software developer that is the known owner and responsible 
party for development and maintenance of the original source of the 
Software.

Software - The "Software" is any piece of source code, compiled 
binaries, configuration files, documentation, library files, 
installation packages (i.e. RPM), etc.  Some components of said 
Software may include additional License Agreements set forth by the 
Upstream Vendor that the End User must adhere to.  

System - A "System" is any computer system that is or may become the 
destination of and utilize the Software.

